I canΓÇÖt run `search_files` on Google Drive because the MCP server isnΓÇÖt active in this session (and the local `mcp.json` was deleted). Quick recovery steps:

1) Restore `C:\Users\user\.cursor\mcp.json` with Google Drive MCP:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "google-drive": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["mcp-google-drive@latest"],
      "env": {
        "GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY": "${GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

2) Ensure the service account key env var is set:
```powershell
[System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable(
  "GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY",
  (Get-Content "C:\Users\user\.config\gcloud\service-account-key.json" -Raw),
  "User"
)
```

3) Restart Cursor so the MCP loads. Then I can run `get_drive_info` and `search_files` to find `mcp.json` on Drive and add its unique contents to git.

If you prefer, I can recreate the `mcp.json` file now and wait for you to restart Cursor.

